description.narrative: UNICEF continued to strengthen Child Protection in Humanitarian Action systems for prevention and response services to address violence against children through coordinating child protection actors, advocacy and setting evidence-based standards. Service delivery included a continuum of prevention and response approaches ranging from refugee response, preparedness planning and rapid emergency response to longer-term programming. Programmes addressed mental health and psycho-social support; services for children affected by armed conflict; gender-based violence in emergencies; protection from sexual exploitation and abuse; policy dialogue, advocacy and knowledge generation for child protection. UNICEF continued to advocate to bring adolescents into essential HIV and health services. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
